Allow f5-sdk to pass parameters to requests, that are then appended to the URI.

@zopyx, @willmcgugan 

When reading from a `ZipExtFile`, the buffer is completely discarded if the requested size is larger than `zipfile.ZipExtFile.MIN_READ_SIZE` (default is 4096 bytes). So I added more cases, to make sure the last buffer is never discarded. When reading a large file, as much as possible will be read with a single `read` call, then the remaining `MIN_READ_SIZE-1` bytes will be read independantly so that the underlying stream.

I added a regression test to `TestReadZipFS` (that did not pass before the fixes to `zipfs.py`) as well as more tests to check the underlying stream buffer is never empty after a read operation.

